contents.rsbHtml: Syntax of if expressions
contents.rsbText: '# Syntax of if expressions

contents.rsbHtml:
The basic syntax of if in Dex is

if <condition> then <consequent> [else <alternate>]
contents.rsbText:
'The basic syntax of `if` in Dex is
```
if <condition> then <consequent> [else <alternate>]
```

contents.rsbHtml: It can be a bit confusing, though, because of all the tokens it may make sense to indent.
contents.rsbText: 'It can be a bit confusing, though, because of all the tokens it may make sense to indent.

contents.rsbHtml:
The main rules are:

  • The else clause is optional (regardless of indentation)
  • The then and else keywords can be inline with the preceding code, or indented relative to the if.
  • The code for each arm of the if can be either an inline expression or start a new indentation level (relative to its keyword if that is indented, or relative to the whole if otherwise).
contents.rsbText:
'The main rules are:
- The `else` clause is optional (regardless of indentation)
- The `then` and `else` keywords can be inline with the preceding
  code, or indented relative to the `if`.
- The code for each arm of the `if` can be either an inline expression
  or start a new indentation level (relative to its keyword if that is
  indented, or relative to the whole `if` otherwise).

contents.rsbHtml: This produces four combinations for one-armed if, all of which are legal:
contents.rsbText: 'This produces four combinations for one-armed `if`, all of which are legal:

contents.rsbHtml: :p yield_accum (AddMonoid Float) \ref. if True then ref += 3. if True then ref += 1. ref += 2. if True then ref += 3. if False then ref += 1. ref += 2.
contents.rsbText:
:p
  yield_accum (AddMonoid Float) \ref.
    if True then ref += 3.
    if True then
      ref += 1.
      ref += 2.
    if True
      then ref += 3.
    if False
      then
        ref += 1.
        ref += 2.

contents.rsbHtml:
However, not every one of the 16 concievable combinations makes sense for two-armed if. To wit:

  • If the consequent is indented, it makes no sense to have the else inline (eliminating 4 combinations).
  • If then is inline, there can be no indented else either, because there is no readable level at which to indent it (elimintaing 2 more combinations).
contents.rsbText:
'However, not every one of the 16 concievable combinations makes sense for two-armed `if`.
To wit:
- If the consequent is indented, it makes no sense to have the `else`
  inline (eliminating 4 combinations).
- If `then` is inline, there can be no indented `else` either, because
  there is no readable level at which to indent it (elimintaing 2 more
  combinations).

contents.rsbHtml: The following contrived code block shows all the acceptable configurations:
contents.rsbText: 'The following contrived code block shows all the acceptable configurations:

contents.rsbHtml: :p yield_accum (AddMonoid Float) \ref. # Two-armed `if` with `then` and the consequent both inline. x = if False then 1. else 3. if False then ref += 100. else ref += 1. ref += 2. if False then ref += 200. else ref += x if False then ref += 300. else ref += 1. ref += 2. # Two-armed `if` with `then` indented but the consequent inline. y = if False then 1. else 3. if False then ref += 100. else ref += 1. ref += 2. if False then ref += 200. else ref += y if False then ref += 300. else ref += 1. ref += 2. # Two-armed `if` with `then` and the consequent both indented. if False then ref += 100. ref += 200. else ref += 3. if False then ref += 100. ref += 200. else ref += 2. ref += 4.
contents.rsbText:
:p
  yield_accum (AddMonoid Float) \ref.
    # Two-armed `if` with `then` and the consequent both inline.
    x = if False then 1. else 3.
    if False then ref += 100. else
      ref += 1.
      ref += 2.
    if False then ref += 200.
      else ref += x
    if False then ref += 300.
      else
        ref += 1.
        ref += 2.

    # Two-armed `if` with `then` indented but the consequent inline.
    y = if False
          then 1. else 3.
    if False
      then ref += 100. else
        ref += 1.
        ref += 2.
    if False
      then ref += 200.
      else ref += y
    if False
      then ref += 300.
      else
        ref += 1.
        ref += 2.

    # Two-armed `if` with `then` and the consequent both indented.
    if False
      then
        ref += 100.
        ref += 200.
      else ref += 3.
    if False
      then
        ref += 100.
        ref += 200.
      else
        ref += 2.
        ref += 4.

contents.rsbHtml: Inline else is not allowed after indented consequent, whether the then keyword is indented or not:

'Inline `else` is not allowed after indented consequent, whether the
`then` keyword is indented or not:

contents.rsbHtml:
if True then x = 6 x else 5
97:12: | 97 | x else 5 | ^ Same-line `else` may not follow indented consequent; put the `else` on the next line.
contents.rsbText:
if True
  then
    x = 6
    x else 5

contents.rsbHtml:
if True then x = 6 x else 5
107:10: | 107 | x else 5 | ^ No `else` may follow same-line `then` and indented consequent; indent and align both `then` and `else`, or write the whole `if` on one line.

if True then
  x = 6
  x else 5
